<br>
Greetings – I am Vulrath, a Vah Shir Shaman of the 16th circle and this is the history of my life:<br>
<br>
I was raised as an only cub – this is rather rare as most of my brethren have many litter-mates. My mother Uumielle died in labor shortly after my birth, along with my unborn brothers and sisters. My father Voluriss was a high-level ambassador for the Vah Shir assigned to Shadowhaven and was often away during my early years, so I was partially raised by Spiritist Fehril, one of the High Shamen of Shar Vahl. There was no animosity because of this arrangement – the time I spent with my father was always joyous as well as many fond memories of my Uncle Fehril. I remember my father being there as my paw was pressed into my personal acrylia slate and I became a citizen of the Vah Shir. Through my juvenile years, I was always trying to follow in the paws of my father – studying politics and participating in debates on a wide range of topics. When I reached my 24th season, I was overjoyed to be appointed as a lower-level diplomat to one of the Trade Barons in Shadowhaven.<br>
<br>
        As I made my way through Shadeweaver’s Thicket on my first diplomatic trip to Shadowhaven I was attacked and poisoned by a Saurek Darkclaw where none had been seen for some time – only the quick actions of the Shar Vahl guards in fighting off the creature and carrying my weakened body back to Spiritist Fehril saved my life. With the poison coursing through my veins, the light began to dim, but my Uncle Fehril called upon all the help of the spirits to purge the poison from my body. Due to the extent of my physical wounds, I drifted in and out of a coma for weeks. When I awoke, I was informed of the death of my father in a foiled assassination attempt on one of the Shadowhaven rulers on the same day I was attacked.<br>
<br>
I felt that things couldn’t have gotten worse when I started hearing voices. At first I thought nothing of it – it could have been the effect of the poison. But soon, the voices came more often and louder. Afraid of loosing my mind, I finally went to my uncle with this news. To my surprise he was overjoyed, and explained to me that I was hearing the voices of my spirit ancestors, a rare and greatly admired gift among my people. He explained how he saved me from the poison, and that the great spiritual forces involved in purging the poison from my body had opened my mind to these and other gifts, which he promised to teach me. Honestly, I was very saddened by this newfound ability. My whole life, all I wanted to do was follow in my father’s paws. I was getting ready to find a pretty feline and settle down with cubs of my own, but these events had changed my life beyond repair.<br>
<br>
        To counteract my sadness and grief, I dedicated myself to learning about my newfound abilities from my Uncle and the other Vah Shir shamen. They taught me how to listen to the spirits for guidance and even channel their incredible powers to aid me. With these new powers came the knowledge and guidance of not only my ancestors, but my own past lives, which had even spanned to new worlds and different races of beings. I completed my Dar Khura training in just 2 seasons, but the feelings of loss, sadness and longing for resolution soon returned. I began to feel the need to find something. I wasn’t sure what I was looking for but I could feel a desire to leave my city and family and venture out into the world to find whatever it was. On my 27th naming day, the Elder Spiritist Grawleh approached me, put his paws on my shoulders and told me that the only way to resolve the conflict within me was to follow the will of the spirits and leave Shar Vahl until I found what my soul required. With a heavy heart I said goodbye to my people and set out for Shadowhaven.<br>
<br>
        This is where I am today. I feel the need to find something, but I’m not sure what it is exactly. Worse than this, from my first few days in Shadowhaven, I am beginning to suspect that my father’s murder was no accident. The Trade Baron I was originally assigned to will not see me and noone seems to know where the ruler my father served has gone, but he hasn’t been seen since shortly after my father’s death. My father doesn’t speak to me through the spirits as my other ancestors do, so I feel his soul isn’t at peace as I continue to look for answers.<br>
<br>
These are my goals: to find the answers to the peculiarities surrounding my father’s death and my attack, to venture into the world and not only discover what my soul is looking for but to find it and gain peace, and to use my knowledge of the spirit world to help other adventurers who I travel with.<br>
My years of diplomatic training have fostered a great tolerance of different races and peoples within me. Although I don’t serve a deity as many other races do (I don’t understand this concept – why not listen to the voices of the spirits instead of one single voice?), I believe in the forces of good and will aid in the crusade against the many evil creatures that infect our land.<br>
Vulrath<br>
Vah Shir Shaman of the 16th Circle<br>
