<br>
&lt;What business does he have here?,&gt; she cautiously pondered.<br>
<br>
Rhatha made his way across the room, seemingly not noticing her; but the predator inside of her told her differently.<br>
<br>
A hand casually fell to the Half Elf’s side and the close proximity of her belted whip as she watched the Vah stop to exchange words with another. Keen elven ears easily listened to the conversation, the talk of spirits stirring her curiosity even more.<br>
<br>
With a patience honed by years of the hunt, Journai bid her time - feigning indifference while all the while waiting for her chance to approach. <br>
<br>
&lt;There, he is leaving, &gt; the Ranger thought with no little relief.<br>
<br>
The coast clear, the black clad Ranger dismounted from her perched vantage point – risking the claustrophobia that always threatened to overwhelm her when indoors.<br>
<br>
“Brother Vulrath?,” she asked in a pleasant tone of voice; her manner clearly more relaxed now that Rhatha was gone.<br>
<br>
The Vah that had been speaking with the Animist but moments before, turned his attention to the pretty Half Elf Maiden.<br>
<br>
“I am Journai Fa’Wander. Daughter of the One Mother. Sister to All. Ranger of Tunare... It is always an honor to meet a member of your noble race. I owe your peoples so much...”<br>
<br>
Journai’s eyes lit up with a warmth that betrayed the sincerity of her words.<br>
<br>
“I could not help but overhear you speaking with Brother Rhatha.”<br>
<br>
Utteringthe Vah’s name gave the woman moment to pause, her gaze quickly scanning the shop as if the mere mention of him could somehow summon his presence.<br>
<br>
“Perhaps I could help you on your journey.”<br>
<br>
~Journai Fa'Wander (Jur-Nay Fah-Wander)<br>
